(The Quintessons weren't afriad of the Autobots because they were acting like 
Humans.  I mean hell, Cybertronians were "acting like Humans" four million 
years before 1984.  They were more afriad of the Humans because they were 
unpredictable, probably because the Quints didn't have any info on 'em.  Or 
just bad writing.

I agree with the Cybertron-Earth relations.  But again, kinda bad writing 
since it left a major player out of it.  Good job Bob Skir.  It wouldn't be a 
problem in BW really since it was a Cybertronian crew lost and the Maximal 
government didn't know about the whole Past Earth thing, only the Tripredacus 
Council did.)
